com.xilinx.rapidwright.device

Class Package

  • Object
    • com.xilinx.rapidwright.device.Package

  • public class Package
extends Object
    Represents an instance of a specific package for a part. Keeps references back to the parent device and can choose from different speed/temperature grades. Also keeps a mapping for package pins. Created on: Jul 1, 2016

      • getGrades

        public Grade[] getGrades()
        Gets a list of all speed/temperature grade variations for this package

        Vivado Tcl:

        set d [get_property DEVICE [get_property PART [current_project]]];set ds []; foreach p [get_parts -filter DEVICE==$d] {lappend ds "[get_property SPEED $p][get_property TEMPERATURE_GRADE_LETTER $p]"}; lsort -unique $ds

        Returns:
        the grades All grade combinations for this package
        Since:
        2018.2.0

      • getSiteType

        public String getSiteType(String packagePinName)
        Gets the site type connected to this package pin or the ball type if no site is connected.

        Vivado Tcl:

        get_property SITE_TYPE [get_sites -of [get_package_pins $packagePin]]

        Parameters:
        packagePinName - Name of the package pin
        Returns:
        The site type connected to the package pin or ball type if none is connected.
        Since:
        2018.2.0

      • getSiteFromPackagePin

        public Site getSiteFromPackagePin(String packagePinName)
        Gets the site associated with the provided package pin name

        Vivado Tcl:

        get_sites -of [get_package_pins $packagePin]

        Parameters:
        packagePinName - Name of the package pin (i.e. B12)
        Returns:
        The site in the device that corresponds to the package pin, or null if no site is connected to that pin.
        Since:
        2018.2.0
